annotations<- read.csv("/Users/lscpuser/Desktop/Childes_corpora_Clara.csv")
annotations<- rename(annotations, corpus_name = Corpus)
d_transcripts <- get_transcripts()
## Using current database version: '2020.1'.
d_statistics <- get_speaker_statistics()
## Using current database version: '2020.1'.
#mean utt and speaker per corpus
n_utt_d<- d_statistics  %>%  group_by(corpus_id) %>% summarize(n_utt=sum(num_utterances)) #count number of utts per corpus
n_utt_speaker <- d_statistics  %>% filter(!(speaker_role=="Target_child")) %>% group_by(corpus_id) %>% summarize(n_speakers=length(unique(speaker_role)))
mergedChiAnnot <- annotations %>% left_join(d_transcripts)
## Joining, by = "corpus_name"
mergedChiAnnot <- mergedChiAnnot %>% left_join(n_utt_d)
## Joining, by = "corpus_id"
mergedChiAnnot <- mergedChiAnnot %>% left_join(n_utt_speaker)
## Joining, by = "corpus_id"
mergedChiAnnot<-mergedChiAnnot[!(is.na(mergedChiAnnot$n_utt) | mergedChiAnnot$n_utt=="" ), ]

if ( length(unique(mergedChiAnnot$corpus_name)) < nrow(annotations) ) {
corpora_not_merged <- nrow(annotations) - length(unique(mergedChiAnnot$corpus_name))
print(corpora_not_merged)} #print non merged corpora
## [1] 20
if (mergedChiAnnot$Inclusion=="yes"){
mergedbyLang<- mergedChiAnnot %>% group_by(Language) %>% nest()}
## Warning in if (mergedChiAnnot$Inclusion == "yes") {: the condition has length >
## 1 and only the first element will be used
mergedbyLang<-mergedbyLang[!(is.na(mergedbyLang$Language) | mergedbyLang$Language=="" ), ]
mergedbyLang_ <- mergedbyLang %>% mutate (count_target_child = map(.x=data, .f=~length(unique(.x$target_child_id)), na.rm = T))

mergedbyLang_<-mergedbyLang_[!(is.na(mergedbyLang_$count_target_child) | mergedbyLang_$count_target_child=="" ), ]
mergedbyLang_<-mergedbyLang_ %>% unnest(count_target_child)

mergedbyLang_ <- mergedbyLang_ %>% mutate (corpus_id = map(.x=data, .f=~length(unique(.x$corpus_id)), na.rm = T))
mergedbyLang_<-mergedbyLang_ %>% unnest(corpus_id)

mergedbyLang_ <- mergedbyLang_ %>% mutate (n_utt_total = map(.x=data, .f=~sum(unique(.x$n_utt)), na.rm = F))
mergedbyLang_<-mergedbyLang_ %>% unnest(n_utt_total)

mergedbyLang_ <- mergedbyLang_ %>% mutate (n_utt_mean = map(.x=data, .f=~mean(unique(.x$n_utt)), na.rm = F))
mergedbyLang_<-mergedbyLang_ %>% unnest(n_utt_mean)

mergedbyLang_ <- mergedbyLang_ %>% mutate (n_sp_mean = map(.x=data, .f=~mean(unique(.x$n_speakers)), na.rm = F)) ######! should loop number of corpora
mergedbyLang_<-mergedbyLang_ %>% unnest(n_sp_mean)
require(scales)
## Loading required package: scales

ggplot(mergedbyLang_, aes(y=Language, x=count_target_child)) + geom_point() + ggtitle("Number of target children per language")+ scale_x_continuous(labels = comma)

ggplot(mergedbyLang_, aes(y=Language, x=corpus_id)) + geom_point() + ggtitle("Number of corpora per language")+ scale_x_continuous(labels = comma)

ggplot(mergedbyLang_, aes(y=Language, x=n_utt_total)) + geom_point() + ggtitle("Total number of utterances per language")+ scale_x_continuous(labels = comma)

ggplot(mergedbyLang_, aes(y=Language, x=n_utt_mean)) + geom_point() + ggtitle("Mean number of utterances per corpus per language") + scale_x_continuous(labels = comma)

ggplot(mergedbyLang_, aes(y=Language, x=n_sp_mean)) + geom_point() + ggtitle("Mean number of speaker roles per corpus per language") + scale_x_continuous(labels = comma)
